ou (and tell you to stop calling them coding ninjas).About your instructor:Hi, I\'m Evan Kimbrell. I too struggled to learn the basics of programming. If failing to program were a sport, I\'d be on the Dream Team. Today, I run a web and mobile development agency called Sprintkick and over the last 4 years we\'ve built and managed over 100+ web &amp; mobile applications. How does one so technologically challenged manage to pull this off? Well, first off I would disagree with \"technologically challenged\" (come on) and second it was actually straight forward. I just had to spend a concerted amount of time learning what I needed to know about basic computer, web, and programming technology as well as modern technology trends and advanced concepts. This course is an accelerated path designed to get you to \"I get it\" and finally start communicating correctly &amp; effectively about technology.','English','Beginner Level',471,77,4.90000,'https://www.udemy.com/pre-programming-everything-you-need-to-know-before-you-code/','https://udemy-images.udemy.com/course/750x422/881980_fc8f.jpg'),('d921ea55df124f53ae2fbe8f95efc0bc','Java fundamentals fast and simple','Course Description\n      \n      \n        \n          Course DescriptionLearn the basics of the Java programming language. Understand concepts for loops, while loops, if statements, try-catch statements, basic data types, object oriented programming to include classes, inheritance, encapsulation, sub-classes and other Java concepts.A review of basic data types and class usage to include common Java data types.Build\n a strong foundation of development with Java. This course helps you \nunderstand Java and the Eclipse IDE.Java 1.7 programming languageEclipse 4Professional skills and experience from an iOS Architect with over 8 years experience.Learn\n the fundamentals but also tips and tricks of the experts. Learn about development with the most widely used programming language for commercial web development and one 